Design a class named Bike to represent a bike. The class contains:
A public constant named DEFAULT_COLOR with the value "black".
A private String data field named color that specifies the bike's color (the default is DEFAULT_COLOR).
A private boolean data field named isInMotion that specifies whether the bike is in motion (the default is false).
The accessor and mutator methods for both data fields.
A no-argument constructor that creates a default bike.
A method named toString() that returns a string description of the bike. 
If the bike is in motion, the method returns "The bike is in motion, color: <color>".
If the bike is not in motion, it returns "The bike is stationary, color: <color>".
Write a test program in Java that creates two Bike objects:
Set the first bike's color to "red" and set it to be in motion.
Keep the second bike with default values.
Display the objects by invoking their toString() method.
Expected Output:
The bike is in motion, color: red
The bike is stationary, color: black


